
Overview of noun illumination

The noun illumination has 5 senses (first 2 from tagged texts)
                                   
1. (2) light, illumination -- (a condition of spiritual awareness; divine illumination; "follow God's light")
2. (1) illumination -- (the degree of visibility of your environment)
3. clarification, elucidation, illumination -- (an interpretation that removes obstacles to understanding; "the professor's clarification helped her to understand the textbook")
4. illuminance, illumination -- (the luminous flux incident on a unit area)
5. miniature, illumination -- (painting or drawing included in a book (especially in illuminated medieval manuscripts))
